$!
You must apply to Natural England for a licence to release non-native species into the wild.
$!

You can get an application form from [Natural England.](http://www.naturalengland.org.uk/ourwork/regulation/wildlife/licences/applicationforms.aspx#11 "Natural England"){:rel="external"}  

You must have a licence to release or grow in the wild an animal or plant that's listed in [Schedule 9 of the Wildlife and Countryside Act 1981 (PDF, 89KB)](https://secure.fera.defra.gov.uk/nonnativespecies/downloadDocument.cfm?id=375 "List of prohibited species (PDF, 89KB)"){:rel="external"}

^You can search for information on non-native species on the [Non-native species secretariat website.](https://secure.fera.defra.gov.uk/nonnativespecies/factsheet/index.cfm "Search for information on non-native species"){:rel="external"}^
